modules.description: This module defines SVG attribute constructors for creating and manipulating vector graphics elements. It provides functions for setting visual properties like dimensions, colors, and transformations, using strings to represent attribute values. Concrete use cases include building SVG shapes with specific styling, such as circles with defined radii, paths with stroke colors, or grouped elements with opacity settings.

This module provides functions to create and manipulate SVG elements such as `circle`, `rect`, `ellipse`, and `polygon`, each accepting attributes and child elements to define structured vector graphics. It works with attribute lists and element trees to build visual components with precise styling and layout properties. Concrete use cases include rendering interactive diagrams, data visualizations, and custom UI elements directly in the browser.

Creates an HTML `style` attribute with the specified CSS property and value. Works with strings to define inline styles for HTML elements. Useful for dynamically applying styles like `color` or `font-size` directly in virtual DOM nodes.

This module creates and manipulates DOM elements with support for attributes and styles. It provides functions to construct SVG elements using a specified namespace, apply attributes and styles, and manage element properties through attribute lists. Concrete use cases include building interactive UI components and rendering SVG graphics directly in the browser.

This module enables rendering interactive vector graphics and UI components by constructing and manipulating DOM and SVG elements with positional, stylistic, and event-driven properties. It operates on data structures like shapes (circles, polygons, text), screens, rectangles, and browser events, providing functions to convert application logic into visual elements and handle user input. Specific applications include building responsive playground interfaces, converting browser interactions to app-specific events, and dynamically adjusting graphical layouts based on screen dimensions.
